fields.description: List of content types on which compression applies. The value should be a valid MIME type.
fields.name: ContentTypesToCompress

fields.description: A reference to the origin group.
fields.name: DefaultOriginGroup

fields.description: A policy that specifies the delivery rules to be used for an endpoint.
fields.name: DeliveryPolicy

fields.description: List of rules defining the user's geo access within a CDN endpoint. Each geo filter defines an access rule to a specified path or content, e.g. block APAC for path /pictures/
fields.name: GeoFilters

fields.description: Indicates whether content compression is enabled on CDN. Default value is false. If compression is enabled, content will be served as compressed if user requests for a compressed version. Content won't be compressed on CDN when requested content is smaller than 1 byte or larger than 1 MB.
fields.name: IsCompressionEnabled

fields.description: Indicates whether HTTP traffic is allowed on the endpoint. Default value is true. At least one protocol (HTTP or HTTPS) must be allowed.
fields.name: IsHTTPAllowed

fields.description: Indicates whether HTTPS traffic is allowed on the endpoint. Default value is true. At least one protocol (HTTP or HTTPS) must be allowed.
fields.name: IsHTTPSAllowed

fields.description: Specifies what scenario the customer wants this CDN endpoint to optimize for, e.g. Download, Media services. With this information, CDN can apply scenario driven optimization.
fields.name: OptimizationType

fields.description: The host header value sent to the origin with each request. This property at Endpoint is only allowed when endpoint uses single origin and can be overridden by the same property specified at origin.If you leave this blank, the request hostname determines this value. Azure CDN origins, such as Web Apps, Blob Storage, and Cloud Services require this host header value to match the origin hostname by default.
fields.name: OriginHostHeader

fields.description: A directory path on the origin that CDN can use to retrieve content from, e.g. contoso.cloudapp.net/originpath.
fields.name: OriginPath

fields.description: Path to a file hosted on the origin which helps accelerate delivery of the dynamic content and calculate the most optimal routes for the CDN. This is relative to the origin path. This property is only relevant when using a single origin.
fields.name: ProbePath

fields.description: Defines how CDN caches requests that include query strings. You can ignore any query strings when caching, bypass caching to prevent requests that contain query strings from being cached, or cache every request with a unique URL.
fields.name: QueryStringCachingBehavior

fields.description: List of keys used to validate the signed URL hashes.
fields.name: UrlSigningKeys

fields.description: Defines the Web Application Firewall policy for the endpoint (if applicable)
fields.name: WebApplicationFirewallPolicyLink
